        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In revision 25118 the file Zend_Application_Resource_Db is changed. With this change the Zend_Db_Table default adapter is set to a string instead of a Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract instance.\r\n\r\nThese lines:\r\n{code:title=Zend_Application_Resource_Db.php|borderStyle=solid}\r\nif ($this->isDefaultTableAdapter()) {\r\n    Zend_Db_Table::setDefaultAdapter($adapter);\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAre removed from 'init()' and placed into 'getDbAdapter()', and uses $adapter which is a string in this case.\r\n\r\nPossible work around (application\/Bootstrap.php):\r\n{code:title=Bootstrap.php|borderStyle=solid}\r\npublic function _initDb ()\r\n{         \r\n    $aConfig = $this->getOptions();\r\n       \r\n    $oAdapter = Zend_Db::factory($aConfig['resources']['db']['adapter'], $aConfig['resources']['db']['params']);\r\n        \r\n    Zend_Db_Table::setDefaultAdapter($oAdapter);        \r\n}\r\n{code}"
        },
